ommon.  See also  Alun ."]},{"name":"Albert","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Albert</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ednyfed ap Ieuan was born about 1350, in Bagillt, Flintshire, Wales, his father, Ieuan ap Bleddyn, was 32 and his mother, Mrs. Ieuan ap Bleddyn, was 28. He had at least 2 daughters with Mrs. Ednyfed ap Ieuan."},"et":{"ABT    1350–":"umbes 1350–Surnud","1350–Male":"1350–Surnud","1354–Female":"1354–Surnud","1392–Female":"1392–Surnud","1394–Female":"1394–Surnud","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1324–Female":"1324–Surnud","Abt 1394":"umbes 1394","1324":"1324","1354":"1354","ABT    1350":"umbes 1350","1320":"1320","ABT    1392":"umbes 1392","1394":"1394","1350":"1350","1392":"1392","of Bagillt,Flint,Flintshire,Wales":"Bagillt, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT    1350–":"noin 1350–Kuollut","1350–Male":"1350–Kuollut","1354–Female":"1354–Kuollut","1392–Female":"1392–Kuollut","1394–Female":"1394–Kuollut","1320–Male":"1320–Kuollut","1324–Female":"1324–Kuollut","Abt 1394":"noin 1394","1324":"1324","1354":"1354","ABT    1350":"noin 1350","1320":"1320","ABT    1392":"noin 1392","1394":"1394","1350":"1350","1392":"1392","of Bagillt,Flint,Flintshire,Wales":"Bagillt, Flintshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT    1350–":"environ 1350–Décédé","1350–Male":"1350–Décédé","1354–Female":"1354–Décédée","1392–Female":"1392–Décédée","1394–Female":"1394–Décédée","1320–Male":"1320–Décédé","1324–Female":"1324–Décédée